premise_source_doc_sentence: The first Olympic champions were both Americans : Thomas Burke in the men 's category and , 32 years later , Betty Robinson in the women 's category .
At old , bronze medallist Collins became the oldest ever world medallist for the men 's 100 m.
Bolt and Spearmon were the two semi-final winners , while the third-fastest , 19-year-old Alonso Edward , demonstrated medal winning form .

In the 100 m final defending champion Usain Bolt caused an upset by false starting -- Yohan Blake had made a slight movement but Bolt was the one who left his blocks , being immediately disqualified .

Nine men have achieved the 100 metres and 200 metres ` Double ' at the same Olympic Games - Archie Hahn  (  1904  )  , Ralph Craig  (  1912  )  , Percy Williams  (  1928  )  , Eddie Tolan  (  1932  )  , Jesse Owens  (  1936  )  , Bobby Morrow  (  1956  )  , Valeriy Borzov  (  1972  )  , Carl Lewis  (  1984  )  , and Usain Bolt  (  2008 , 2012 , 2016  )  .
